Dataset Description
Dataset Name: MNIST (Modified National Institute of Standards and Technology)

Source: Available on Kaggle, Yann LeCun's Website, or via tensorflow.keras.datasets

Type of Data: Image data (grayscale images of handwritten digits)

Number of Samples:

Training set: 60,000 images

Test set: 10,000 images

Image Dimensions: 28 Ã— 28 pixels (784 features per image)

Format: Each image is represented as a 1D array of 784 pixel values (flattened), with an associated label (digit 0â€“9)

Target Variable: Digit class (from 0 to 9)

Data Type: Structured (numerical image pixel data)

Static or Dynamic: Static

Balanced: Yes â€” roughly equal distribution of each digit class

